  "prompt": "How is Modi different from Kejriwal?",
  "response": "Here are some key differences between Narendra Modi and Arvind Kejriwal:\n\n1. Political Party\n- Modi: Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP)\n- Kejriwal: Aam Aadmi Party (AAP)\n\n2. Political Background\n- Modi: Long-time RSS and BJP worker, Chief Minister of Gujarat\n- Kejriwal: Former bureaucrat, anti-corruption activist turned politician\n\n3. Political Ideology\n- Modi: Right-wing, Hindu nationalist\n- Kejriwal: Left-leaning, anti-corruption platform\n\n4. Governance Style\n- Modi: Centralized, strong leadership approach\n- Kejriwal: More grassroots, welfare-oriented approach\n\n5. National vs Regional Focus\n- Modi: National level, Prime Minister of India\n- Kejriwal: Primarily focused on Delhi state politics\n\n6. Electoral Success\n- Modi: Won two consecutive national elections\n- Kejriwal: Successful in Delhi state elections\n\n7. Communication Style\n- Modi: Charismatic, powerful public speaker\n- Kejriwal: More direct, confrontational communication\n\n8. Economic Approach\n- Modi: Pro-business, market-oriented reforms\n- Kejriwal: Welfare-focused, more socialist-leaning policies\n\nThese differences highlight their distinct political personas and approaches to governance.",
